England captain Wayne Rooney was in buoyant mood as he linked up with the rest of the squad for the first time since being named captain.

The 28-year-old was named as Steven Gerrard's successor last week, which would have topped off a exciting few weeks for the Manchester United forward, after just recently being made captain for his club side.

Just 10 outfield players were deemed fit enough to take part in England's first training session since their disappointing World Cup campaign. 

