The other 13 players, including goalkeepers Joe Hart, Ben Foster and Fraser Forster, trained as normal on a wet morning at Arsenal's Hertfordshire training base.

England, who finished bottom of their World Cup group, face Norway at Wembley on Wednesday and then fly to Basle five days later to take on Switzerland in their first Euro 2016 qualifier.

As a result of England's poor World Cup showing, the Football Association are expecting a record low crowd of between 35,000 and 40,000 at Wembley on Wednesday.

 

 

 

